en_23621_0	All Brigades and Units under the Security Force Headquarters - Mullaittivu (SFHQ-MLT) giving a further fillip to the Army-initiated cultivation programmes, took steps to plant hundreds of mango and coconut saplings inside their compounds on the instructions of the Commander, Security Forces - Mullaittivu (SF-MLT).
en_23621_1	To begin with, during a simple arrangement on Friday (10), Major General Dushyantha Rajaguru, Commander, SF-MLT, together with Brigadier General Staff, Brigadier W.D.C.K Costa, Brigadier Admin and Quartering, Colonel E.P Hennadige and a team of Officers and Other Ranks planted 155 mango and 50 coconut saplings in the SFHQ-MLT premises and gave the lead to the project.
en_23621_2	Similarly, 150 mango saplings, provided by the SFHQ-MLT to the 64 Division Headquarters in Oddusuddan were planted in three separate demarcated zones by Senior Officers at the 64 Division Headquarters on the same day (10).
en_23621_3	Instructors of the Department of Agriculture will follow up the entire cultivation project until those plants grow up fully.
en_23621_4	Those species of plants include Alponsu and Karthakolomba mangoes.
en_23621_5	All the Officers and Other Ranks joined the programme.
